WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:07.006
♪

00:07.008 --> 00:08.073
<i>(frustrated growl)</i>

00:10.744 --> 00:12.111
What's wrong, twilight?

00:12.113 --> 00:17.249
And there isn't a single mention
of the mysterious chest

00:17.251 --> 00:19.084
That came from the
tree of harmony.

00:19.086 --> 00:21.453
Nor anything about
keys to unlock it.

00:21.455 --> 00:25.457
But something tells me that
opening it is pretty important.

00:25.459 --> 00:28.027
I hope princess
celestia has some ideas.

00:28.029 --> 00:30.129
If the library in canterlot
doesn't have anything,

00:30.131 --> 00:32.064
I don't know where
else to look.

00:32.066 --> 00:33.532
<i>(crash)</i>

00:34.535 --> 00:38.804
My dearest twilight, while it
would be perfectly lovely

00:38.806 --> 00:41.040
To have you in
canterlot once more,

00:41.042 --> 00:42.408
I have another
option in mind

00:42.410 --> 00:44.676
Much closer to ponyville...

00:44.678 --> 00:46.712
<i>Celestia: As you know,</i>
<i>the ancient castle</i>

00:46.714 --> 00:48.814
<i>That I once shared</i>
<i>with princess luna</i>

00:48.816 --> 00:52.818
<i>Lies mostly in ruins deep</i>
<i>in the everfree forest.</i>

00:52.820 --> 00:55.554
<i>But if you look carefully,</i>
<i>you may find a book</i>

00:55.556 --> 00:57.656
<i>That could prove helpful</i>
<i>to your research</i>

00:57.658 --> 01:01.060
<i>Hidden somewhere in what's</i>
<i>left of the castle library.</i>

01:02.762 --> 01:04.396
<i>(gasp)</i>

01:06.399 --> 01:09.334
Wow! Look at all
these ancient books.

01:09.336 --> 01:11.737
It's a veritable gold
mine of information.

01:11.739 --> 01:14.706
I can't believe
it! Woo-hoo!

01:14.708 --> 01:15.841
Whoa!

01:15.843 --> 01:17.142
<i>(crash)</i>

01:18.645 --> 01:19.678
Gah!

01:19.680 --> 01:25.250
Heh, heh. So, twilight.
Uh, ready to head home?

01:25.252 --> 01:26.585
Are you kidding?

01:26.587 --> 01:28.387
This place is perfect!

01:29.489 --> 01:33.092
<i>(chattering)</i>

01:36.629 --> 01:40.365
<i>♪ my little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:40.367 --> 01:41.834
<i>♪ aaaaahhh!</i>

01:41.836 --> 01:46.705
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be ♪</i>

01:46.707 --> 01:48.674
<i>♪ my little pony</i>

01:48.676 --> 01:50.843
<i>♪ until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me ♪</i>

01:50.845 --> 01:52.177
<i>♪ big adventure</i>

01:52.179 --> 01:57.449
<i>♪ it's an easy feat</i>

01:57.451 --> 02:01.587
<i>♪ my little ponies</i>

02:01.589 --> 02:04.423
<i>♪ do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:04.425 --> 02:08.694
♪

02:16.137 --> 02:19.872
Rainbow dash: I'm not
gonna move. You move.

02:19.874 --> 02:24.176
Applejack: Uh-uh. There's
no way I'm moving.

02:24.178 --> 02:26.645
This is the most daring
dare any pony ever dared

02:26.647 --> 02:28.480
Dare another pony to dare.

02:28.482 --> 02:29.615
Both: Huh?

02:29.617 --> 02:30.849
It's exciting!

02:30.851 --> 02:35.220
<i>(buzzing)</i>

02:35.222 --> 02:38.790
Rainbow dash and applejack are
competing for the title

02:38.792 --> 02:40.626
Of most daring pony.

02:40.628 --> 02:42.494
This is the final test.

02:42.496 --> 02:43.929
The bee stare.

02:43.931 --> 02:46.498
Last pony to blink wins.

02:46.500 --> 02:49.334
I'm gonna need my bees back.

02:49.336 --> 02:54.206
But then we'll never find out
who the most daring pony is.

02:54.208 --> 02:55.607
Sorry about that.

02:55.609 --> 02:56.742
<i>(beckoning whistle)</i>

02:59.179 --> 03:00.946
Well, what do we do now?

03:00.948 --> 03:04.950
Don't worry ladies, I've been
keeping excellent score all day.

03:04.952 --> 03:08.720
Hmm. Move the decimal,
carry the two, and ...

03:08.722 --> 03:09.821
Congratulations!

03:09.823 --> 03:11.290
You're tied!

03:11.292 --> 03:16.328
You can't be tied for
the most daring pony.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.630
Numbers don't lie.

03:22.502 --> 03:24.403
I'd love to stay and
keep keeping score,

03:24.405 --> 03:26.405
But I promised to help
test the new school bell.

03:26.407 --> 03:29.208
I get to ring it
all week non-stop.

03:29.210 --> 03:30.742
And I don't even
have to take turns

03:30.744 --> 03:32.244
Because no one
else volunteered!

03:32.246 --> 03:33.779
<i>(giggle)</i>

03:33.781 --> 03:35.647
Ok. No problem.

03:35.649 --> 03:38.317
We just have to come up
with another daring dare.

03:38.319 --> 03:39.384
Right.

03:44.557 --> 03:46.892
I think I might have an
idea of what we can do.

03:50.797 --> 03:53.932
Um... Rarity, don't you think
it's a little late in the day

03:53.934 --> 03:55.734
To be walking through
the forest?

03:55.736 --> 03:59.271
<i>It is star spider</i>
<i>season, after all.</i>

03:59.273 --> 04:02.007
Though I'm sure you have
a very good reason...

04:02.009 --> 04:05.711
Simply the most important reason
I've ever had in my entire life.

04:05.713 --> 04:07.879
Oh. Well, then I'm
happy to help.

04:07.881 --> 04:12.251
I've heard rumors that the
castle of the two sisters

04:12.253 --> 04:14.987
Is filled with the most gorgeous
of ancient tapestries

04:14.989 --> 04:17.389
In all of pony history.

04:17.391 --> 04:20.259
It pains me to think of those
magnificent creations

04:20.261 --> 04:24.329
Rotting away in those old
ruins, totally unappreciated.

04:24.331 --> 04:26.331
I see.

04:26.333 --> 04:29.401
I require your help in
borrowing one or two

04:29.403 --> 04:31.703
To bring back to the boutique
where I can restore them.

04:31.705 --> 04:34.373
Maybe I'll even use the
patterns as the inspiration

04:34.375 --> 04:36.275
For a new line.

04:36.277 --> 04:37.876
That does sound...

04:37.878 --> 04:39.845
Very important.

04:39.847 --> 04:42.447
Yes, well, maybe not the
most important thing

04:42.449 --> 04:45.284
In my entire life,

04:45.286 --> 04:47.519
But retro-ancient
classical will be all the rage

04:47.521 --> 04:49.888
Next season, so it's
nothing to sneeze at.

04:49.890 --> 04:50.922
<i>(sneeze)</i>

04:52.892 --> 04:58.730
<i>♪ (eerie)</i>

04:58.732 --> 05:01.600
Um, are you sure you
need those tapestries?

05:01.602 --> 05:06.772
Although, I must admit,
these ruins are a fright.

05:06.774 --> 05:09.641
Look at all the
dirt everywhere.

05:09.643 --> 05:10.709
Ew.

05:11.878 --> 05:13.345
(gasp) angel!

05:17.850 --> 05:20.952
<i>♪ (threatening)</i>

05:20.954 --> 05:24.523
It's practically an
artistic treasure trove

05:24.525 --> 05:26.425
Of ancient good taste.

05:28.528 --> 05:31.396
Angel, you really shouldn't
have run off like that.

05:31.398 --> 05:33.565
Ancient ruins are filled with
all sorts of things

05:33.567 --> 05:37.502
You could stub your toe
or trip on a loose stone.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.104
You have to be careful.

05:44.744 --> 05:46.878
Spike: I don't think I'll need
all these candles, twilight.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.747
I was really only
scared for a second.

05:48.749 --> 05:50.482
Oh, these aren't
for you, spike.

05:50.484 --> 05:52.351
We're going to be studying
late into the night

05:52.353 --> 05:54.419
And we're going to need
all the light we can get.

05:54.421 --> 05:55.787
Oh. Great.

05:57.824 --> 06:00.459
Applejack: Well? Here we are!

06:00.461 --> 06:03.428
What's so daring
about this place?

06:03.430 --> 06:05.764
This is where we got the
elements of harmony.

06:05.766 --> 06:08.533
When I was just a filly,
grannie smith told me

06:08.535 --> 06:10.135
Of an ancient legend...

06:10.137 --> 06:12.537
When nightmare
moon was banished,

06:12.539 --> 06:16.007
Not every last bit of her
dark magic went with her.

06:16.009 --> 06:20.412
<i>Grannie used to say when</i>
<i>night falls on the castle,</i>

06:20.414 --> 06:23.548
That magic takes the form of...

06:23.550 --> 06:26.651
The pony hoof shadows.

06:26.653 --> 06:28.653
You mean like a ghost?

06:28.655 --> 06:32.424
(ghostly voice)
no pony knows.

06:32.426 --> 06:33.458
Ugh!

06:34.093 --> 06:35.060
<i>(gasp)</i>

06:35.062 --> 06:37.462
This one is perfect!

06:37.464 --> 06:41.566
Well, it certainly could
use some restoration.

06:41.568 --> 06:44.536
Fly up there and lift
it off that hook.

06:47.006 --> 06:50.442
<i>(struggling whimpers)</i>

06:50.444 --> 06:52.077
Maybe from below?

06:54.947 --> 06:56.581
<i>(clatter)</i>

06:56.583 --> 06:57.783
<i>(rumble)</i>

06:57.785 --> 06:58.984
<i>(slam)</i>

07:00.653 --> 07:03.655
I don't see what's so
daring about an old legend.

07:03.657 --> 07:07.025
Plus, I don't
believe in ghosts.

07:07.027 --> 07:09.995
You might wanna re-think
your position on that.

07:09.997 --> 07:11.997
<i>(frightened screams)</i>

07:13.466 --> 07:14.566
<i>(screams)</i>

07:14.568 --> 07:15.700
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

07:16.502 --> 07:17.903
<i>(high-pitched screams)</i>

07:19.105 --> 07:20.172
<i>(high-pitched screams)</i>

07:20.174 --> 07:21.940
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

07:21.942 --> 07:23.508
You saw that, right?

07:23.510 --> 07:24.709
Run!

07:25.912 --> 07:27.813
<i>(rumbling)</i>

07:27.815 --> 07:29.114
<i>(slam)</i>

07:29.116 --> 07:31.950
Ow, I think I hurt my wing.

07:31.952 --> 07:34.219
Oh, my dear, I
am so sorry.

07:34.221 --> 07:35.821
That tapestry is
far too heavy.

07:35.823 --> 07:37.789
We'll just have to
find a smaller one.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.925
Oh. Of course.

07:39.927 --> 07:42.027
Where, pray tell, did
you disappear to?

07:42.029 --> 07:43.728
What do you mean?

07:43.730 --> 07:45.530
While you were struggling
under that fabric,

07:45.532 --> 07:47.599
The entire wall
spun around.

07:47.601 --> 07:49.668
You must have activated
a secret door.

07:49.670 --> 07:51.937
Oh, I'm sorry.

07:51.939 --> 07:54.806
I suppose these ruins
are chock-full of them.

07:54.808 --> 07:55.874
Really?

07:55.876 --> 07:58.944
We must use the
utmost care as we...

07:58.946 --> 07:59.945
<i>(screams)</i>

08:01.681 --> 08:02.914
<i>(slam)</i>

08:03.951 --> 08:08.153
Rainbow dash: Ok. So
maybe the legend is true.

08:08.155 --> 08:10.088
Well, that's why I
brought you here.

08:10.090 --> 08:12.491
I guess only the most
daring pony of all

08:12.493 --> 08:13.892
Could stay in this
castle all night

08:13.894 --> 08:15.160
Without
being scared off.

08:16.028 --> 08:17.829
<i>(skid)</i>

08:17.831 --> 08:18.897
Scared?

08:18.899 --> 08:20.198
I'm not scared.

08:20.200 --> 08:22.167
Well, me neither!

08:22.169 --> 08:28.206
Whoever stays in the castle the
longest is the most daring pony.

08:29.642 --> 08:30.742
Deal!

08:30.744 --> 08:35.013
But it's gonna take a lot more
than some shadowy ghost pony

08:35.015 --> 08:36.948
To get me to leave.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.517
Me, too.

08:46.526 --> 08:47.893
Find anything, spike?

08:47.895 --> 08:48.894
<i>(thud)</i>

08:48.896 --> 08:50.128
Uh... Nope.

08:50.130 --> 08:51.530
Nothing yet.

08:52.566 --> 08:54.566
<i>(rumbling)</i>

08:54.568 --> 08:56.635
What are you doing here?

08:58.004 --> 08:59.638
<i>(whoosh)</i>

09:01.874 --> 09:03.041
<i>(gasp)</i>

09:07.847 --> 09:11.116
The journal of the
two sisters.

09:11.118 --> 09:14.719
Maybe this is the book princess
celestia was talking about!

09:16.222 --> 09:19.724
I sure hope you're not afraid
of the dark, applejack.

09:19.726 --> 09:22.761
I can't say that I am,
but even if I was,

09:22.763 --> 09:24.863
I'd be at least fifty percent
less scared of it

09:24.865 --> 09:26.698
Than you, rainbow dash.

09:27.934 --> 09:30.035
I don't know how all
that math works because

09:30.037 --> 09:31.670
I'm not scared at all.

09:31.672 --> 09:32.804
Me neither.

09:33.973 --> 09:34.940
Huh?

09:36.842 --> 09:38.910
What's the matter?

09:38.912 --> 09:44.215
It's just a dark hallway full
of disembodied pony legs.

09:44.217 --> 09:47.786
Yeah. Nothing
creepy about that.

09:51.324 --> 09:53.692
<i>Rarity: I'm starting to</i>
<i>wonder if maybe this castle</i>

09:53.694 --> 09:55.660
<i>Doesn't want my expertise.</i>

09:56.929 --> 09:57.963
Oh, dear.

09:57.965 --> 09:59.064
Angel?

09:59.066 --> 10:00.932
Rarity, have you seen him?

10:00.934 --> 10:03.735
I'm not sure he made the
trip down with us, dear.

10:03.737 --> 10:04.869
Oh, goodness.

10:04.871 --> 10:08.239
An ancient castle is
no place for a bunny.

10:08.241 --> 10:10.041
He could get hit
by falling debris

10:10.043 --> 10:11.876
Or the floor could
give out under him.

10:11.878 --> 10:16.081
Oh! He could be trapped in a
dark place with no way out.

10:16.083 --> 10:18.683
I can only imagine
how that might feel.

10:19.819 --> 10:21.019
Hmmm.

10:21.021 --> 10:25.290
<i>♪ (ominous)</i>

10:25.292 --> 10:29.327
Applejack, if you're scared,
you can just admit it.

10:29.329 --> 10:31.696
You don't need to put
your hoof around me.

10:31.698 --> 10:34.833
Applejack: Uh... I'm over here.

10:37.970 --> 10:43.108
<i>(screams)</i>

10:43.110 --> 10:44.109
<i>(gasp)</i>

10:44.111 --> 10:46.044
Rarity, what is it?

10:46.046 --> 10:47.812
I felt something.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.280
Alive!

10:49.282 --> 10:50.782
Angel!

10:55.655 --> 10:56.354
<i>(whirring)</i>

10:56.356 --> 11:01.026
Well, tapestries or no, I have
had just about enough

11:01.028 --> 11:03.962
Of secret passages,
mysterious presences

11:03.964 --> 11:05.830
And unappreciative castles.

11:07.734 --> 11:11.936
Not with angel lost somewhere
in this dangerous old castle.

11:11.938 --> 11:14.706
He could be trapped
under a crumbling statue

11:14.708 --> 11:18.276
Or stuck high in a tower
without food or water

11:18.278 --> 11:20.912
(sobbing) or any friends at all!

11:20.914 --> 11:22.914
<i>(crunch)</i>

11:22.916 --> 11:25.183
Spike, you've got to hear this.

11:25.185 --> 11:27.419
I love to duck behind
the paintings

11:27.421 --> 11:30.722
Still gives her a
bit of a fright,

11:30.724 --> 11:33.725
The trap door slide
is luna's favorite.

11:33.727 --> 11:36.227
Hall of hooves?

11:36.229 --> 11:38.963
Soon the organ to the
outside will be finished.

11:38.965 --> 11:40.865
I can hardly wait.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.802
What's the organ
to the outside?

11:43.804 --> 11:45.403
I have no idea.

11:52.978 --> 11:55.714
<i>♪ (blasting chord)</i>

11:55.716 --> 11:57.348
<i>(skid)</i>

11:57.350 --> 11:58.717
Do you hear that?

11:58.719 --> 12:03.088
You mean the creepy sound
of a haunted pipe organ?

12:03.090 --> 12:05.356
Uh... Maybe.

12:05.358 --> 12:07.726
I don't know what
you're talking about.

12:07.728 --> 12:09.260
<i>♪ (pipe organ chord)</i>

12:12.131 --> 12:14.232
Uh, twilight?

12:14.234 --> 12:15.867
Did you hear something?

12:15.869 --> 12:18.837
Quit being such
a scaredy dragon.

12:18.839 --> 12:20.839
This castle is
thousands of years old

12:20.841 --> 12:23.141
And half of it was destroyed
by nightmare moon.

12:23.143 --> 12:25.110
Of course it makes
strange sounds;

12:25.112 --> 12:26.778
It's practically
falling apart.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.379
<i>(clatter)</i>

12:28.381 --> 12:30.215
<i>(giggle)</i>

12:30.217 --> 12:31.816
Ok.

12:33.152 --> 12:37.188
Angel? Angel?

12:37.190 --> 12:38.857
I'm sure we'll find him.

12:40.359 --> 12:41.292
Angel?

12:41.294 --> 12:43.928
<i>(rarity shouts)</i>

12:44.864 --> 12:45.830
Did you find angel?

12:45.832 --> 12:47.031
Is he ok?

12:47.033 --> 12:47.999
<i>(gasp)</i>

12:48.001 --> 12:50.401
They are perfect!

12:50.403 --> 12:53.071
No castle in its right mind
could possibly object

12:53.073 --> 12:55.774
To my restoring such
exquisite works of art.

12:55.776 --> 12:57.942
Oh, they're lovely, rarity,

12:57.944 --> 13:00.812
But I have to keep
looking for angel.

13:00.814 --> 13:04.082
I hope he doesn't think
I've given up on him.

13:04.084 --> 13:05.416
I'm right behind you.

13:05.418 --> 13:08.353
Won't be a moment...

13:13.025 --> 13:15.126
Applejack: Do you think there's
a single room in this castle

13:15.128 --> 13:17.495
That isn't filled with
terrifying things?

13:20.232 --> 13:21.299
Whoa!

13:21.301 --> 13:22.967
Heh heh.

13:22.969 --> 13:24.869
It's just old pony armor.

13:24.871 --> 13:25.970
What's the big deal?

13:25.972 --> 13:29.474
It's not like it's going
to come to life or anything.

13:29.476 --> 13:30.875
Right?

13:36.182 --> 13:37.148
<i>♪ (pipe organ chord)</i>

13:37.150 --> 13:38.016
Huh?

13:38.018 --> 13:39.050
<i>(thunk)</i>

13:39.819 --> 13:40.952
<i>(scream)</i>

13:40.954 --> 13:42.053
♪

13:42.055 --> 13:43.121
<i>(squeal)</i>

13:44.089 --> 13:45.089
<i>(scream)</i>

13:45.091 --> 13:46.090
♪

13:46.092 --> 13:47.325
<i>(pop)</i>

13:48.294 --> 13:50.295
♪

13:50.297 --> 13:51.296
<i>(frightened shout)</i>

13:52.531 --> 13:54.065
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

13:54.067 --> 13:55.500
Whoa!

13:57.269 --> 13:58.203
<i>(gasp)</i>

13:59.905 --> 14:02.173
<i>(shrill scream)</i>

14:03.409 --> 14:07.011
<i>♪ (organ)</i>

14:08.514 --> 14:10.148
<i>♪ (eerie)</i>

14:10.150 --> 14:11.282
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

14:13.252 --> 14:16.020
<i>(gasp)</i>

14:16.022 --> 14:18.189
Now, you look here, castle.

14:18.191 --> 14:20.992
You are very old and
very scary,

14:20.994 --> 14:23.461
But your wall art is
in an atrocious state

14:23.463 --> 14:25.196
<i>(whistling wind)</i>

14:25.198 --> 14:27.265
And there is nothing you
can do to keep me

14:27.267 --> 14:29.267
From my sacred task
of restoration.

14:30.636 --> 14:33.371
Uh, applejack?

14:33.373 --> 14:36.941
If you went back to
ponyville, that means I win.

14:36.943 --> 14:38.309
Right?

14:38.311 --> 14:39.510
<i>(clatter)</i>

14:39.512 --> 14:40.478
<i>(crash)</i>

14:40.480 --> 14:42.213
<i>(scream)</i>

14:44.617 --> 14:46.184
Rarity?

14:48.053 --> 14:50.622
I know hiding isn't really
your sense of humor,

14:50.624 --> 14:53.191
But please let this be a joke.

14:57.396 --> 14:58.296
<i>♪ (organ blast)</i>

14:58.298 --> 14:59.998
<i>(scream)</i>

15:00.566 --> 15:01.432
<i>(shout)</i>

15:07.306 --> 15:09.040
Rainbow?

15:09.042 --> 15:10.275
Hello?

15:13.212 --> 15:17.282
I guess if I don't find you,
I win by default. Right?

15:22.321 --> 15:24.689
<i>(crashing)</i>

15:24.691 --> 15:25.957
Oof!

15:27.660 --> 15:28.626
<i>(growl)</i>

15:28.628 --> 15:34.232
This is by far the
most ungrateful.

15:34.234 --> 15:35.533
Oof!

15:35.535 --> 15:38.136
(thunderclap and whistling wind)

15:42.675 --> 15:44.242
(whisper) angel!

15:44.244 --> 15:46.277
Rarity?

15:46.279 --> 15:49.213
Oh, I hope you two
are together.

15:49.215 --> 15:50.949
<i>(rumbling)</i>

15:56.221 --> 15:57.088
<i>(frightened shout)</i>

15:58.457 --> 16:01.292
Haunted statues, creepy armor...

16:01.294 --> 16:04.128
Come on, castle, is
that all you got?

16:04.130 --> 16:05.263
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

16:12.237 --> 16:14.639
<i>(screams of terror)</i>

16:14.641 --> 16:20.611
<i>(whimpers and shouts)</i>

16:20.613 --> 16:26.985
I was only trying to restore
ancient (sobbing) art!

16:26.987 --> 16:28.720
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

16:28.722 --> 16:29.520
<i>(gasp)</i>

16:29.522 --> 16:30.455
Angel?

16:30.457 --> 16:31.589
<i>(grunts)</i>

16:31.591 --> 16:32.590
<i>(cracking)</i>

16:32.592 --> 16:33.624
<i>(crash)</i>

16:33.626 --> 16:36.461
Angel!

16:36.463 --> 16:37.595
<i>(rumble)</i>

16:37.597 --> 16:39.230
What it the world is that?

16:39.232 --> 16:44.035
Probably just more strange
sounds of this old castle

16:44.037 --> 16:46.004
Falling apart.

16:46.006 --> 16:47.772
No one likes sarcasm, spike.

16:51.076 --> 16:54.278
<i>(screams)</i>

16:54.280 --> 16:56.014
What got into them?

16:56.016 --> 16:59.384
<i>(screams)</i>

16:59.386 --> 17:00.385
It's ok, angel.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.186
You're ok. You're ok!

17:02.188 --> 17:03.254
<i>(yell)</i>

17:03.256 --> 17:05.023
Shadows everywhere!

17:05.025 --> 17:07.191
<i>(screams)</i>

17:07.193 --> 17:09.694
<i>(sobbing)</i>

17:09.696 --> 17:11.796
Angel!

17:11.798 --> 17:13.698
All right. Everypony stop!

17:16.468 --> 17:17.502
Twilight?

17:17.504 --> 17:18.302
Must.

17:18.304 --> 17:19.504
Save.

17:19.506 --> 17:20.438
Angel.

17:21.707 --> 17:22.673
Oh.

17:23.475 --> 17:24.475
Fluttershy?

17:24.477 --> 17:25.777
What are you doing here?

17:25.779 --> 17:27.245
She's with me.

17:32.618 --> 17:34.652
Thank you!

17:34.654 --> 17:36.187
Have you all spent
the whole night

17:36.189 --> 17:38.256
Running around
scaring each other?

17:38.258 --> 17:40.458
Well, that depends.

17:40.460 --> 17:42.193
On what?

17:42.195 --> 17:45.563
On whether or not you're
the pony of shadows?

17:45.565 --> 17:48.199
What's the pony of shadows?

17:48.201 --> 17:50.468
Oh, that's just an
old pony's tale.

17:50.470 --> 17:52.804
<i>♪ (pipe organ)</i>

17:52.806 --> 17:55.740
Then who's playing that?

17:55.742 --> 17:57.442
We're going to find out.

17:57.444 --> 18:07.652
♪

18:07.654 --> 18:24.836
♪

18:24.838 --> 18:26.771
<i>(collective gasp)</i>

18:26.773 --> 18:28.473
The pony of shadows!

18:28.475 --> 18:38.683
♪

18:38.685 --> 18:44.455
♪

18:44.457 --> 18:47.225
Did you know I can
totally play the organ?

18:47.227 --> 18:48.593
Because I didn't.

18:48.595 --> 18:50.661
Pinkie!

18:50.663 --> 18:53.631
<i>♪ (baseball cheer)</i>

18:53.633 --> 18:56.234
You're the pony
of shadows?

18:56.236 --> 18:57.835
The pony of what?

18:57.837 --> 18:59.871
See? What did I tell you?

18:59.873 --> 19:02.306
I thought you had to ring
the school bell all week.

19:02.308 --> 19:05.143
I only had to ring
it for like, five minutes.

19:05.145 --> 19:06.310
They said that was good enough.

19:06.312 --> 19:07.678
I can't imagine why.

19:07.680 --> 19:11.149
<i>(clanging)</i>

19:11.151 --> 19:12.617
So, then I decided to throw a

19:12.619 --> 19:14.619
Finished ringing the
school bell party,

19:14.621 --> 19:20.491
Without bluebells so I went to
everfree forest to pick some,

19:20.493 --> 19:24.395
I had to wrap myself up in
the tarp I was going to use

19:24.397 --> 19:29.667
Before I could invite
them to my party.

19:29.669 --> 19:33.171
So I could help you all
with your party.

19:33.173 --> 19:34.805
What party is that?

19:34.807 --> 19:37.241
Uh, the everypony come to
the scary old castle

19:37.243 --> 19:39.410
And hide from each other while
I play the organ party.

19:40.279 --> 19:41.379
<i>(boing)</i>

19:41.381 --> 19:42.346
<i>(thud)</i>

19:42.814 --> 19:43.881
Duh!

19:51.323 --> 19:53.658
I swear this is going right
back where I found it

19:53.660 --> 19:57.228
Just as soon as I've returned
it to its former glory.

19:57.230 --> 19:59.797
Now don't go running off again.

19:59.799 --> 20:02.633
Ooh. I can't believe I
was so frightened.

20:02.635 --> 20:05.403
I guess I let my imagination
get the best of me.

20:05.405 --> 20:07.305
I think we all did.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.674
I always let my imagination
run away from me.

20:09.676 --> 20:11.876
Then it comes back with cake.

20:13.512 --> 20:15.947
Well, it's good to know that
whenever your imagination

20:15.949 --> 20:19.684
Is getting away from you, a good
friend can help you rein it in.

20:19.686 --> 20:21.419
And even though I didn't
find anything out

20:21.421 --> 20:23.354
About the mysterious chest,

20:23.356 --> 20:25.556
I'm glad I was here to
help all of you.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.658
You certainly did
that, twilight.

20:27.660 --> 20:30.962
Yeah, why weren't you scared?

20:30.964 --> 20:33.731
Reading celestia's diary
made it hard to be afraid

20:33.733 --> 20:36.667
Because I knew what it was like
when she and luna lived here.

20:36.669 --> 20:40.671
Made it easier to deal with my
problems in the present,

20:40.673 --> 20:42.707
Even the scary ones.

20:42.709 --> 20:45.643
<i>(murmurs of agreement)</i>

20:46.712 --> 20:48.879
I just thought of a great idea!

20:48.881 --> 20:50.481
Why don't we keep a journal?

20:50.483 --> 20:52.683
Just like the royal
pony sisters?

20:52.685 --> 20:53.718
All of us?

20:53.720 --> 20:57.421
Sure! That way we can
learn from each other.

20:57.423 --> 20:59.624
And maybe someday other
ponies will read it

20:59.626 --> 21:01.359
And learn something too.

21:01.361 --> 21:03.661
What a splendid idea!

21:03.663 --> 21:05.963
I know what my
first entry will be.

21:05.965 --> 21:10.768
Dear diary, I'm glad grannie
smith's legend wasn't true.

21:10.770 --> 21:12.503
Me too.

21:12.505 --> 21:14.839
Me three, because
that means you two

21:14.841 --> 21:18.442
Are still tied for
most daring pony!

21:20.846 --> 21:22.947
Ha! Shadow ponies.

21:22.949 --> 21:25.049
How ridiculous is that?

21:25.051 --> 21:27.451
<i>♪ (eerie)</i>

21:27.453 --> 21:29.920
♪
